es/colors.xml | high | 2 | 2 | 2 | planned:2 |\n223: | app/src/main/res/values/ic_launcher_background.xml | high | 2 | 2 | 2 | planned:2 |\n224: | app/src/main/res/values/strings.xml | high | 5 | 5 | 5 | planned:5 |\n225: | app/src/main/res/values/themes.xml | high | 3 | 3 | 3 | planned:3 |\n226: | gradle.properties | high | 3 | 3 | 3 | planned:3 |\n227: | settings.gradle.kts | high | 1 | 1 | 1 | planned:1 |\n228: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/presentation/util/Screen.kt | medium | 1 | 0 | 0 | planned:1 |\n229: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/ui/theme/Color.kt | medium | 1 | 0 | 0 | planned:1 |\n230: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/ui/theme/Shape.kt | medium | 1 | 0 | 0 | planned:1 |\n231: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/ui/theme/Theme.kt | medium | 1 | 0 | 0 | planned:1 |\n232: | app/src/main/java/com/example/foodike/ui/theme/Type.kt | medium | 1 | 0 | 0 | planned:1 |\n233: \n234: ## Test Harness Status\n235: \n236: | field | value |\n237: | --- | --- |\n238: | available | False |\n239: | acceptedPass | False |\n240: | environmentStatus | unknown |\n241: | latestPhase |  |\n242: | latestResult |  |\n243: | latestPhaseMatchesCurrent | False |\n244: | referencedTestCount | 5 |\n245: | targetTestPackagePresent | True |\n246: | targetTestFiles | 6 |\n247: | sdkOrEnvironmentBlockerSuspected | False |\n248: \n249: ### Test Harness Notes\n250: \n251: - No test build report is available yet.\n252: - Current phase references tests; record a PASS, focused manual/emulator evidence, or a harness blocker.\n253: \n254: ## Test Hints\n255: \n256: - string key coverage check\n257: - placeholder preservation check\n258: - locale selection smoke test\n259: - manual review of descriptor/resource mapping\n260: - build_hap_report.py --phase phase-01-project-skeleton-resources\n261: \n262: ## Instructions\n263: \n264: - Start with implementationGroups as the current phase implementation contract: implement each group, then use mustComplete entries as exact row-level checks.\n265: - Use planContract as upstream planning ownership evidence; resolve its alignmentFindings by updating plannedPhase/matrix/platform evidence or by documenting sourceOverride/analysisGap when source inspection disagrees.\n266: - Keep grouped business behavior discoverable through precise target endpoints; avoid closing unrelated features only through root/shell/whole-file endpoints.\n267: - Merge source files only when it improves target clarity and still preserves per-feature evidence, tests, and controllable file size.\n268: - Treat mustComplete entries as the current phase's executable row-level task list.\n269: - Use behaviorAudit as the current phase behavior audit; it checks closed critical/high rows for source behavior, target behavior, parity, and verification evidence.\n270: - Use uiContract entries as static-analysis planning aids, not complete UI specifications: preserve listed source-visible screen structure, route/back behavior, actions, state feedback, and visual evidence needs, then re-read source/resources/navigation for UI behavior the static analysis may have missed.\n271: - Do not close the phase while current-phase critical/high entries are open, weakly deferred, or missing evidence.\n272: - For every closed critical/high source feature, record sourceBehavior, targetBehavior, parityLevel, targetEndpoints, and verificationEvidence in source-coverage-matrix.json.\n273: - A build pass alone is not per-feature verification; cite tests, manual/emulator evidence, or explicit verificationEvidence for behavior closure.\n274: - Use implemented-simplified only with concrete simplification reason, preserved-behavior explanation, target endpoints or tests, and source/platform evidence.\n275: - If a suitable HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package exists for a platform capability, use it or record a platform replacement; do not close the item with local mock data, sample data, in-memory simulation, or another fallback.\n276: - Use deferred only for concrete blockers; otherwise implement faithfully or platform-replace with evidence.\n277: - Update source-coverage-matrix.json/md and platform-capability-check.json/md before phase completion.\n278: - If this checklist is empty but the phase has real scope in plan.md/plan.json, assign plannedPhase values first.\n\n(End of file - total 278 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Task Checklist\n\n- Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n\n## Purpose\n\nCurrent-phase task checklist generated from the agent-maintained source coverage matrix and platform capability check. Use it before editing and update the matrix/check after work.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phaseFeatureEntries | 49 |\n| phaseCriticalHighFeatureEntries | 44 |\n| mustCompleteFeatureEntries | 28 |\n| needsEvidenceFeatureEntries | 0 |\n| deferredOrFallbackFeatureEntries | 3 |\n| coveredFeatureEntries | 13 |\n| phaseSourceFiles | 19 |\n| phasePlatformCapabilityEntries | 1 |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-task-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782532709256,"end":1782532709262}},"id":"prt_f073a9b70001Qqr9ENaDXwlYnW","sessionID":"ses_0f8c58db4ffemy4EKnbgXc6BxW","messageID":"msg_f073a89c0001VbQ7jZH7dm7KOv"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1782532709314,"sessionID":"ses_0f8c58db4ffemy4EKnbgXc6BxW","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fNv79f1eEsNNHv0H69qjE69T","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\phase-capability-checklist.md"},"output":"<path>D:\\workspace\\Foodike\\translation-inputs\\phase-capability-checklist.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Phase Platform Capability Pre-Resolution\n2: \n3: - Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n4: \n5: ## Purpose\n6: \n7: Phase-scoped platform capability pre-resolution checklist. This is generated from phase-task-checklist.json and platform-capability-check.json before phase implementation. All current-phase critical/high platform capabilities must be resolved before target code edits begin.\n8: \n9: ## Summary\n10: \n11: | metric | value |\n12: | --- | --- |\n13: | phasePlatformCapabilities | 1 |\n14: | unresolvedPlatformCapabilities | 0 |\n15: | compileProbeRecommendedCapabilities | 0 |\n16: | discoveryOnlyCapabilities | 0 |\n17: | sdkProbeDeclarationCandidateCapabilities | 1 |\n18: \n19: ## Resolution Status Counts\n20: \n21: | resolution status | count |\n22: | --- | --- |\n23: | resolved-real-api | 1 |\n24: \n25: ## Unresolved Platform Capabilities\n26: \n27: _No unresolved current-phase platform capabilities._\n28: \n29: ## All Current-Phase Platform Capabilities\n30: \n31: | capability id | importance | platform status | resolution | decision | probe | sdk cache | capability | target API/library | reason |\n32: | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- | --- |\n33: | localization-resources | high | verified-direct | resolved-real-api | resolved-real-api |  | declaration-candidate | Localized resources and formatted strings | HarmonyOS Cangjie LocalizationKit resource model (`ohos.base.ResourceStr`, `ohos.resource.AppResource`, `ohos.resource_manager.ResourceManager`) with standard HarmonyOS `string.json`/`color.json` resources | explicit direct API/Kit/package resolution |\n34: \n35: ## Instructions\n36: \n37: - If any entry is unresolved, run a capability resolution session before phase implementation.\n38: - Capability resolution may update only platform-capability-check.json/md.\n39: - A real HarmonyOS/Cangjie API, Kit, example, or package must be used when available; do not close with local mock, in-memory data, sample data, or generic fallback.\n40: - Use resolved-deferred only after checking CangjieSkills/HarmonyOS/Cangjie docs, HarmonyOS-Examples, SDK declarations, and package lookup when relevant.\n41: - Use capability-sdk-probe-cache.json as preparation evidence for SDK declaration/library candidates; it is not authority by itself.\n42: - Treat ArkTS/native/overview declarations as discovery-only until a Cangjie-callable API, wrapper, FFI, bridge, or compile probe is recorded.\n43: - When compileProbeRecommended is true, run a bounded target-context compile probe or record the concrete SDK/tooling blocker before phase implementation.\n\n(End of file - total 43 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Phase Platform Capability Pre-Resolution\n\n- Phase: `phase-01-project-skeleton-resources`\n\n## Purpose\n\nPhase-scoped platform capability pre-resolution checklist. This is generated from phase-task-checklist.json and platform-capability-check.json before phase implementation. All current-phase critical/high platform capabilities must be resolved before target code edits begin.\n\n## Summary\n\n| metric | value |\n| --- | --- |\n| phasePlatformCapabilities | 1 |\n| unresolvedPlatformCapabilities | 0 |\n| compileProbeRecommendedCapabilities | 0 |\n| discoveryOnlyCapabilities | 0 |\n| sdkProbeDeclarationCandidateCapabilities | 1 |\n\n## Resolution Status Counts\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"translation-inputs\\phase-capability-checklist.md","time":{"start":1782532709308,"end":1782532709313}},"id":"prt_f073a9b8a0014Zo9gTBllduoqj","sessionID":"ses_0f8c58db4ffemy4E